														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3589336">
									

<p>I liked it. Not too much here to be said; the writing in the earlier sections didn't sit quite right with me, but it picks up later when they begin to really get in the thick of it, oddly enough. I was just reading in the discussion section of another tale earlier today about the importance of character placement (and, incidentally, how the article in question lacked it.) This has that; I never felt question about where anybody stood in my mental depiction of the events as they occurred. This could be resultant of the fact that a good chunk of it is Bert sitting in his truck stewing in a pit of nerves and anguish (very much enjoyed that bit) but there's still a good bit of movement later on when the reinforcements come on scene.</p>
<p>Overall - it does what it sets out to do well, and what it set out to do fit within my niche quite nicely.</p>

							</div>

								
					
